title: Holes-in-one for Central New York golfers (Oct. 8)
text:
Following is the list of holes-in-one made recently by Central New York golfers:
Jim Bubnack , Sept. 13, at the 135-yard 15th hole at Links at Marcellus Golf Club using a 6-iron. Witnessed by Bob Lane, Brian Smith and Tim Burns.
Jim Griffin , Sept. 16, at the 297-yard 5th hole at Cazenovia Golf Club using a driver. Witnessed by Riley Holmes, Geoff Snyder and Max Cooper.
Dan Kinsella , Sept. 25, at the 140-yard 11th hole at Arrowhead Golf Course using a 6-iron. Witnessed by Jeff Shell, Kevin Foran and Kyle Storie.
Gary Coloismo , Sept. 26, at the 150-yard 13th hole from the white tees at the Links at Erie Village using a 6-iron. Witnessed by Randy Lacelle, John Vongel, Jeff Voss and Cayla DiSalvo.
Karen Schmidt , Oct. 4, at the 139-yard 2nd hole at Radisson Greens using a hybrid. Witnessed by Bill George.
Tom Ryan , Oct. 4, at the 130-yard 13th hole at Millstone Golf Course using a 9-iron. Witnessed by Pam Ward and Terry Clark.
Michael Kalet , Oct. 4, at the 170-yard 12th hole at Drumlins Country Club East Course using a 3-wood. Witnessed by Steve Volinsky, John Renock and Mike Gordon.
Rita Bratek , Oct. 5, at the 125-yard 8th hole at Drumlins Country Club East Course using a 7-wood. Witnessed by Pat McGrath, Gary Kittell and Liz Kittell.
Ed Coolican , Oct. 7, at the 124-yard (senior tees) 13th hole at the Links at Erie Village using a 4-hybrid. Witness by Ron Genest.
Editor's note:
Syracuse.com will recognize three special golf accomplishments on a weekly basis this year: holes-in-one, double eagles and shoot your age (18-hole scores that match or are below a golfer's age).
Send details by email only to Fran Piraino at mfpiraino1@yahoo.com.
Please include the name of golfer, date, hole number, yardage, course name, club used and names of witnesses. For authenticity, it is preferred that the reports come from golf course personnel.
